2.2.2 Ectopic Interval Correction

Four correction techniques are described to replace ectopic intervals found during the

detection process. The first technique is to simply remove any ectopic intervals found.

Simple ectopic interval removal has been shown to be as effective as other replacement

methods [56]. Another method replaces any ectopic interval with the mean value of w

neighboring IBI intervals centered on the ectopic interval using Equation (2.3) .

